{"id":"antothite","term":"Antothite","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>An inhabitant of Anathoth, found only in <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 11:28\">1 Chr. 11:28</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 12:3\">12:3</a>. In <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Samuel 23:27\">2 Sam. 23:27</a> it is Anethothite; in <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 27:12\">1 Chr. 27:12</a>, Anetothite. (R.V., “Anathothite.”)</p>\n\u0000","refs":["1 Chronicles 11:28","1 Chronicles 12:3","2 Samuel 23:27","1 Chronicles 27:12"]}